@startuml Amdox-ERP-Sequence
title Amdox ERP — How the parts connect (real workflow)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam maxMessageSize 220

actor User
participant "React + Vite\n(Axios + Zustand)" as FE
participant "Express API\n:5000\n(routes/index.ts)" as API
participant "Middleware\nauthenticate /\nrequirePermission /\nvalidate(Joi)" as MW
participant "Controller\n(req → res)" as CTRL
participant "Service\n(business logic)" as SVC
database "PostgreSQL 17\nvia Prisma" as DB
participant "Redis\n(sessions, tokens)" as RD
participant "ML Service\nFastAPI :8000\n(LSTM+Prophet)" as ML
participant "Gmail SMTP\n(Nodemailer)" as MAIL

' ============================================================
== 1. Register Company (public) ==
User -> FE : fill register form
FE -> API : POST /api/v1/auth/register
API -> MW : validate(registerSchema)
MW -> CTRL : ok → authController.register
CTRL -> SVC : authService.register()
SVC -> DB : create Tenant + admin User + default Roles
SVC -> SVC : bcrypt.hash(password)
SVC --> CTRL : { user, accessToken, refreshToken }
CTRL --> FE : 201 + JWT
FE -> FE : store token + user (Zustand / localStorage)

' ============================================================
== 2. Login → JWT ==
User -> FE : email + password
FE -> API : POST /api/v1/auth/login
API -> MW : validate(loginSchema)
MW -> CTRL : authController.login
CTRL -> SVC : authService.login()
SVC -> DB : find User + roles + permissions
SVC -> SVC : bcrypt.compare()
SVC -> DB : INSERT Session + AuditLog
SVC --> CTRL : tokens (JWT carries tenantId + permissions)
CTRL --> FE : 200 + accessToken (+ refresh cookie)
note over FE : Axios interceptor now attaches\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\nto every request

' ============================================================
== 3. Authenticated request — the 5-layer chain (e.g. Record Payment) ==
User -> FE : submit payment form
FE -> API : POST /api/v1/finance/payments\n(Bearer token)
API -> MW : authenticate (verify JWT)
MW -> RD : check session valid
RD --> MW : ok
MW -> MW : requirePermission('finance:write')
MW -> MW : validate(createPaymentSchema)
MW -> CTRL : req.user set → paymentController.create
CTRL -> SVC : paymentService.create({ tenantId, invoiceId, amount })
SVC -> DB : find Invoice (scoped by tenantId)
SVC -> DB : SUM completed payments
SVC -> SVC : guard: approved? not overpaid?
SVC -> DB : $transaction → INSERT Payment\n+ UPDATE Invoice status (PARTIALLY_PAID / PAID)
DB --> SVC : committed
SVC --> CTRL : { payment, newStatus }
CTRL --> FE : 201 "invoice is now PAID" (sendSuccess)
FE --> User : toast + refresh table (TanStack Query)
note over MW, DB : Every query is filtered by tenantId →\nmulti-tenant isolation. Errors bubble to\nerrorHandler middleware → sendError(JSON)

' ============================================================
== 4. AI Demand Forecast (backend ↔ ML service) ==
User -> FE : Generate Forecast
FE -> API : POST /api/v1/supply/forecasts (Bearer)
API -> MW : authenticate + requirePermission('supply:write')
MW -> CTRL : forecastingController.create
CTRL -> SVC : forecastingService.generate(inventoryItemId)
SVC -> DB : read 6+ months of OUT stock movements
DB --> SVC : monthly sales history
SVC -> ML : POST /forecast (axios)\n{ historical_data, model_type }
ML -> ML : LSTM / Prophet → predict + MAPE
ML --> SVC : { forecasts[], model_used, mape }
SVC -> DB : INSERT Forecast rows
SVC --> CTRL : forecast result
CTRL --> FE : 201 + predictions
FE --> User : render chart (Recharts) 📈

' ============================================================
== 5. Forgot Password (Redis token + email) ==
User -> FE : enter email
FE -> API : POST /api/v1/auth/forgot-password
API -> CTRL : authController.forgotPassword
CTRL -> SVC : authService.forgotPassword(email)
SVC -> DB : find User by email
SVC -> RD : SET pwreset:<token> = userId (TTL 15m)
SVC -> MAIL : send reset link (FRONTEND_URL/reset-password?token=…)
MAIL --> User : 📧 reset email
User -> FE : open link → set new password
FE -> API : POST /api/v1/auth/reset-password { token, newPassword }
API -> CTRL : authController.resetPassword
CTRL -> SVC : authService.resetPassword()
SVC -> RD : GET + DEL token (one-time use)
SVC -> DB : UPDATE passwordHash + revoke sessions
CTRL --> FE : 200 "please log in"

' ============================================================
== 6. Event fan-out (notifications + webhooks) ==
SVC -> SVC : eventService.emit('invoice.paid')
SVC -> DB : INSERT Notification (in-app)
SVC -> DB : find active Webhooks subscribed to event
SVC -> SVC : webhookService.deliver() (HMAC-signed POST)
SVC -> DB : INSERT WebhookDelivery (status logged)

' ============================================================
== 7. Audit trail (cross-cutting) ==
note over SVC, DB : Sensitive mutations call auditService.log() →\nhash-chained AuditLog row (tamper-evident).\nGET /audit/verify re-checks the chain.

@enduml
